li.p:
The graph is a parabola that opens to the left. Its vertex is the point (4,-1).  To find another point on the graph, choose a value for y, say y=\alert{3}. Solving for x yields

    (\alert{3} + 1)^2 \amp = -8(x-4) \amp\amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by }-8.}
    \dfrac{16}{-8} \amp = x-4 \amp\amp \blert{\text{Add 4 to both sides.}}
    2 \amp = x

Thus, (2,3) lies on the graph. Because of symmetry, there is another point on the graph with the same x-coordinate and at an equal distance from the parabola's axis, which is the line y=-1. This point is (2,-5), as shown below.

